Title: On the unitarity problem in space/time noncommutative theories
Authors: D. Bahns, S. Doplicher, K. Fredenhagen, G. Piacitelli
Comments: 7 pages; typos corrected, sign convention changed on p.2
Report-no: DESY 02-028, accepted to Physics Letters B
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Quantum Algebra
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B533 (2002) 178-181
\\
  It is shown that the violation of unitarity observed in space/time
noncommutative field theories is due to an improper definition of quantum field
theory on noncommutative spacetime.
